The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar is scheduled to meet with governors of the party. The meeting is aimed at concluding plans on who emerges as Atiku’s running mate ahead of the 2023 elections. A notice of the meeting was made public by the Secretariat of the PDP Governors Forum, signed by the Director-General of the PDP GF, CID Maduagbanam. The notice said the meeting started at the Legacy House in Abuja, at 2:30pm. Atiku is yet to pick his running mate since emerging the PDP’s presidential candidate. However, some names like Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State and Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State have been fingered as possible candidates to be picked